The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 25 September is 3,391 (392.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 21 September, there were 109 new confirmed cases (12.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 September, there were 120 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 9% (11 fewer cases).
